wer wicks and closes that consistently fail to recover intraday losses.\n\nThe structure story here is one of a well-defined short-term downtrend losing momentum as it approaches a prior reaction zone. The 1.22111 area served as a pivot on multiple occasions through June, attracting sellers on at least three distinct approaches \u2014 that level now sits as overhead resistance should any recovery attempt materialise. Below it, the 1.21241 zone acted as a brief consolidation shelf before the pair broke lower in early July, and it too would need to be reclaimed before any bullish structural argument could be made. The more immediate reference is the 1.20415 prior reaction zone, which capped a bounce attempt on 10 July before sellers reasserted themselves. Price has now moved through that level and is testing the 1.19797 structure support, a zone that has attracted two prior reactions and represents the clearest near-term floor the chart offers.\n\nOn the hourly timeframe, the picture is one of grinding, low-volatility pressure. Since the sharp drop on 9 July, the H1 bars have been notably compressed in range, suggesting the initial momentum has faded but that buyers have not yet shown any conviction. The brief spike to 1.20241 during the European morning on 15 July was quickly faded, and the subsequent drift back towards 1.1984 keeps the short-term path of least resistance pointing lower. There is no clear H1 base forming at present \u2014 the price action looks more like a slow bleed than a capitulation low.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes the prospect of data-driven volatility spikes in either direction. With no scheduled catalysts, price action is likely to remain technically driven and range-bound unless broader risk sentiment shifts materially across the commodity currency complex. Thin conditions can occasionally produce exaggerated moves through key levels, so the proximity to 1.19797 support is worth monitoring closely.\n\nThe desk's neutral bias reflects the tension between a clear directional move lower and the proximity to structural support. A sustained hourly close below 1.19797 would suggest that level has been absorbed and could open the path towards the 1.1930 area. Conversely, any recovery that recaptures 1.20415 on a daily closing basis would begin to question the short-term bearish structure and shift attention back towards the mid-range. Until one of those scenarios resolves, the chart sits in a genuinely ambiguous position.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}